FBIS3-36635 "drsov026_a_94014" FBIS-SOV-94-026 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Delegations To Draw Up Nuclear Arms Measures LD0402202294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1643 GMT 4 Feb 94 LD0402202294 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [From the "Diplomatic Panorama" feature] [Text] A Russian delegation is due to leave for Kiev on February 8 to draw up, jointly with Ukrainian officials, a set of measures to implement the Russian-Ukrainian-U.S. agreements on nuclear weapons, the head of the delegation said. Yuriy Dubinin told Interfax the delegation would include Nuclear Energy Minister Viktor Mikhailov and a senior Defense Ministry official, Colonel-General Yevgeniy Maslin. Russia "is always open for bilateral negotiations with Ukraine and is ready to help organize a trilateral meeting with the participation of the United States," Dubinin said.
